(26, 1, 'Here''s the simple ajax call to the text file which would return the content the targeted text fil\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Step 1 :</strong> Create a new .php and .txt file\n\n<strong>Step 2 :</strong> In the .php file include the jquery minimal version\n<pre class="lang:default decode:true">&lt;script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.2/jquery.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;</pre>\n<strong>Step 3 :</strong> Introduce a trigger and a result area\n<pre class="lang:default decode:true">&lt;div id="trigger"&gt;Get the Result&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div id="result"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</pre>\n&nbsp;\n\n<strong>Step 4 :</strong> Write a jquery click event\n<pre class="lang:default decode:true ">$("#trigger").click(function(){\n\n// ajax call here\n\n});</pre>\n<strong>Step 5 :</strong> Place the ajax call over there\n<pre class="lang:default decode:true">$.ajax({url: "demo_test.txt", success: function(result){\n$("#result").html(result);\n}});\n</pre>\n&nbsp;\n\nAnd you''re done !!\n\n<strong>Here''s the code that you look for : </strong>\n<pre class="lang:default decode:true ">&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\n&lt;html&gt;\n&lt;head&gt;\n&lt;script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.2/jquery.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\n&lt;script&gt;\n$(document).ready(function(){\n$("#trigger").click(function(){\n$.ajax({url: "demo_test.txt", success: function(result){\n$("#result").html(result);\n}});\n});\n});\n&lt;/script&gt;\n&lt;/head&gt;\n&lt;body&gt;\n&lt;div id="trigger"&gt;Get the Result&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;div id="result"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\n&lt;/body&gt;\n&lt;/html&gt;</pre>\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\nWell, i won''t say how to create a text file and put content inside it !!', 'Simple jquery ajax call to a .txt file', 'publish', 'simple-jquery-ajax-call-to-a-txt-file', '2015-09-01 09:44:50', '2015-09-01 09:44:50'),
(27, 1, 'Here''s the simple ajax call to the text file which would return the content the targeted text fil\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 1 :</strong> Create a new .php and .txt file\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 2 :</strong> In the .php file include the jquery minimal version\r\n\r\n(javascript)&lt;script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.2/jquery.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;(/javascript)\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 3 :</strong> Introduce a trigger and a result area\r\n\r\n(php)\r\n\r\n&lt;div id="trigger"&gt;Get the Result&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;div id="result"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n(/php)\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 4 :</strong> Write a jquery click event\r\n\r\n(javascript)\r\n\r\n$("#trigger").click(function(){\r\n\r\n// ajax call here\r\n\r\n});\r\n\r\n(/javascript)\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 5 :</strong> Place the ajax call over there\r\n\r\n(javascript)\r\n\r\n$.ajax({url: "demo_test.txt", success: function(result){\r\n$("#result").html(result);\r\n}});\r\n\r\n(/javascript)\r\n\r\nAnd you''re done !!\r\n\r\n<strong>Here''s the code that you look for : </strong>\r\n\r\n(php)\r\n\r\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\r\n&lt;html&gt;\r\n&lt;head&gt;\r\n&lt;script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.2/jquery.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;script&gt;\r\n$(document).ready(function(){\r\n$("#trigger").click(function(){\r\n$.ajax({url: "demo_test.txt", success: function(result){\r\n$("#result").html(result);\r\n}});\r\n});\r\n});\r\n&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;\r\n&lt;body&gt;\r\n&lt;div id="trigger"&gt;Get the Result&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;div id="result"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;/body&gt;\r\n&lt;/html&gt;\r\n\r\n(/php)', 'Simple jquery ajax call to a .txt file', 'inherit', '26-revision-v1', '2015-05-20 09:53:51', '2015-05-20 09:53:51'),
