(44, 1, 'The MySQL is officially <a href="https://wiki.php.net/rfc/mysql_deprecation" target="_blank">depreciated</a> and will be completely removed in php 7.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nYou can see the below given warning message in all posts of <a href="http://php.net/manual/en/function.mysql-affected-rows.php" target="_blank">mysql functions</a> in the php.net website.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://sysaxiom.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mysql_depreciated.png"><img class=" size-medium wp-image-45 aligncenter" src="http://sysaxiom.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mysql_depreciated-300x69.png" alt="mysql_depreciated" width="300" height="69" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\ni.e.,\r\n\r\n<strong>Warning : </strong>\r\n<p class="para">This extension is deprecated as of PHP 5.5.0, and will be removed in the future. Instead, the <a class="link" href="http://php.net/manual/en/book.mysqli.php">MySQLi</a> or <a class="link" href="http://php.net/manual/en/ref.pdo-mysql.php">PDO_MySQL</a> extension should be used. See also <a class="link" href="http://php.net/manual/en/mysqlinfo.api.choosing.php">MySQL: choosing an API</a> guide and <a class="link" href="http://php.net/manual/en/faq.databases.php#faq.databases.mysql.deprecated">related FAQ</a> for more information. Alternatives to this function include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul class="simplelist">\r\n	<li class="member"><span class="function"><a class="function" href="http://php.net/manual/en/mysqli.affected-rows.php">mysqli_affected_rows()</a></span></li>\r\n	<li class="member"><span class="methodname"><a class="methodname" href="http://php.net/manual/en/pdostatement.rowcount.php">PDOStatement::rowCount()</a></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a href="http://stackoverflow.com/a/12860046/3282633" target="_blank">Here</a> is the beautiful answer about this topic.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nAnd to be honest, I suggest everyone to use mysqli''s Object Oriented Style and it will make your code and you smart. And Never stick to w3school''s procedural style as it might make you to think less :)', 'Why one should not use mysql functions', 'publish', 'why-one-should-not-use-mysql-functions', '2015-06-12 06:32:01', '2015-06-12 06:32:01'),
