(174, 1, 'Here''s the simple ajax call to the text file which would return the content the targeted text fil\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 1 :</strong> Create a new .php and .txt file\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 2 :</strong> In the .php file include the jquery minimal version\r\n\r\n&lt;pre class="lang:default decode:true"&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.2/jquery.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;/pre&gt;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 3 :</strong> Introduce a trigger and a result area\r\n\r\n[php]\r\n\r\n&lt;div id="trigger"&gt;Get the Result&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;div id="result"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n[/php]\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 4 :</strong> Write a jquery click event\r\n\r\n[javascript]\r\n\r\n$("#trigger").click(function(){\r\n\r\n// ajax call here\r\n\r\n});\r\n\r\n[/javascript]\r\n\r\n<strong>Step 5 :</strong> Place the ajax call over there\r\n\r\n[javascript]\r\n\r\n$.ajax({url: "demo_test.txt", success: function(result){\r\n$("#result").html(result);\r\n}});\r\n\r\n[/javascript]\r\n\r\nAnd you''re done !!\r\n\r\n<strong>Here''s the code that you look for : </strong>\r\n\r\n[php]\r\n\r\n&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;\r\n&lt;html&gt;\r\n&lt;head&gt;\r\n&lt;script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.11.2/jquery.min.js"&gt;&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;script&gt;\r\n$(document).ready(function(){\r\n$("#trigger").click(function(){\r\n$.ajax({url: "demo_test.txt", success: function(result){\r\n$("#result").html(result);\r\n}});\r\n});\r\n});\r\n&lt;/script&gt;\r\n&lt;/head&gt;\r\n&lt;body&gt;\r\n&lt;div id="trigger"&gt;Get the Result&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;div id="result"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;/body&gt;\r\n&lt;/html&gt;\r\n\r\n[/php]\r\n\r\nWell, i won''t say how to create a text file and put content inside it !!', 'Simple jquery ajax call to a .txt file', 'inherit', '26-revision-v1', '2015-09-01 09:41:18', '2015-09-01 09:41:18'),
